I am not proposing we hold up merging. However, do we have a cheatsheet for fixing these issues?

The build fails as follows:

| WARNING: tmp/work/p10bmc-openbmc-linux-gnueabi/linux-aspeed/6.1.34+gitAUTOINC+aa3bee4aa1-r0/temp/run.do_install.1009838:225 exit 1 from '[ -e Module.symvers ]'
| WARNING: Backtrace (BB generated script):
| 	#1: do_install, tmp/work/p10bmc-openbmc-linux-gnueabi/linux-aspeed/6.1.34+gitAUTOINC+aa3bee4aa1-r0/temp/run.do_install.1009838, line 225
| 	#2: main, tmp/work/p10bmc-openbmc-linux-gnueabi/linux-aspeed/6.1.34+gitAUTOINC+aa3bee4aa1-r0/temp/run.do_install.1009838, line 283

The test will fail, as the file does not exist for our openbmc kernels, but should just mean the install step is skipped:

        [ -e Module.symvers ] && install -m 0644 Module.symvers ${D}/${KERNEL_IMAGEDEST}/Module.symvers-${KERNEL_VERSION}

If I remove this line from kernel.bbclass the build succeeds.

Why is the test for the Module.symvers file causing the script to exit?

This line requires Module.sysvers to exist and the install to succeed, instead of the intended skip the install if it doesn't exist.

Previously there were two additional installs afterwards which changed the result
this points out (1) the whole block is not under sh -e (2) the test should be if then or use inverted logic

Fixes
https://github.com/openembedded/openembedded-core/commit/38dc75c0e5eb7427ffcf201113fb45e0d5dad453

Replace
    [ -e Module.symvers ] && install -m 0644 Module.symvers ${D}/${KERNEL_IMAGEDEST}/Module.symvers-${KERNEL_VERSION}

With

    if [ -e Module.symvers ] ; then
        install -m 0644 Module.symvers ${D}/${KERNEL_IMAGEDEST}/Module.symvers-${KERNEL_VERSION}
    fi

Module.symvers is dependent on CONFIG_MODVERSIONS and Modules (since its in modpost Makefile)

https://github.com/openbmc/linux/blob/aa3bee4aa1ff7988e101ed2f7be68b9e89bd3b5b/scripts/Makefile.modpost#L60C7-L60C25
The problem is exposed by the above, but the source goes back before git into svn.
